## Block certificate

> Headers

```
Content-type: application/json
```

> Body example

```json
{
    "shop_id": "...",
    "shop_secret": "..."
}
```

> Request example

```shell
curl --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --request PATCH \
  --data-binary "@data.json" \
  https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/:code/block
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
  "status": "success"
}
```

Permanently blocks a certificate. Blocked certificate can't be restored.

### HTTP Request

`PATCH https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/:code/block`
### Query Parameters

| Parameter        | Required | Description                                                         |
|------------------|----------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| shop_id          | true     | Your API key                                                        |
| shop_secret      | true     | Your API secret key                                                 |





